code_id: mds
physical: q-ary_digits 
logical: q-ary_digits 

name: 'MDS codes'
#introduced: '\cite{}'
description: 'The Singleton bound states that for linear classical codes, \(d \leq n-k+1\). MDS (maximum distance seperable) codes comprise of any classical linear code that saturates this bound.'
protection: 'Given \(n\) and \(k\), MDS codes have the highest distance possible of all codes and so have the best possible error correction properties (although they might be inefficient).'

